config DRM_VCRTCM_PIM_V4L2
	tristate "Video for Linux PIM"
	depends on DRM_VCRTCM && VIDEO_V4L2
	select VIDEOBUF_VMALLOC
	help
	 PIM for V4L2.  Instantiated PCONs present their pixel
	 stream as a V4L2 device in user space. Allows applications
	 that can take V4L2 input to do something good with the
	 rendered pixels

	 select 'm' or 'n'; 'y' not tested yet


